Operatives of the Bauchi State Police Command have arrested five suspected internet fraudsters undergoing training in the state. The Spokesman of the Command, SP Ahmed Wakil who confirmed the arrest in a statement said the operatives of the command acting on credible intelligence raided a hideout where the suspected cyber criminals were undergoing training in Bauchi metropolis. He said, “The Operatives of the State Intelligence Bureau (SIB), Bauchi Command acted on a verified intelligence on 20th May 2022, burst into an apartment located at Kirfi Road, GRA, Bauchi where a training center was established for the training of youths who want to venture into internet crime.” -Advertisement- According to him, the suspects include Emmanuel Saleh alias Wizblaq, 22; Matthias Akronyi alias Mad Kid, 20, Patience Nuhu, 21, Bulus Haruna, 18, and Kingsley Simon, 19. The police recovered four laptops, one television set, four sound systems, one power generator, seven plastic chairs, one office chair, musical keyboard and a fridge. Wakil however said the Commissioner of Police, Umar Sanda has directed the suspects to be charge to court as soon as investigations were concluded.